The paper discusses challenges in testing quality requirements in a large system-of-systems project in the public sector, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of virtual plumblines, which is a technique used in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The system-of-systems aspect of the project suggests that it could also fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper discusses requirements engineering and architecturally significant requirements, which are topics related to requirements engineering (cs.RE). Finally, the paper discusses solutions proposed in the literature for testing quality requirements, which falls under the software quality (cs.QA) sub-category.
